library("CancerSubtypes")
load("C:/Users/xtsvm/Desktop/Project 6 for BRCA/Dataset/BRCA_mRNA_miRNA_LncRNA_ok.rda")
RNASeqV2_USE=t(RNASeqV2_USE)
miRNASeqHiseq_USE=t(miRNASeqHiseq_USE)
LncRNA_USE=t(LncRNA_USE)

###Feature selection
data1=FSbyMAD(RNASeqV2_USE, cut.type = "topk", value=6000)

data2=FSbyMAD(miRNASeqHiseq_USE, cut.type = "topk", value=400)

data3=FSbyMAD(LncRNA_USE, cut.type = "topk", value=5000)

### z-socre
data1=t(scale(t(data1)))
data2=t(scale(t(data2)))
data3=t(scale(t(data3)))

1. use the mRNA data for CC

result0=ExecuteCC(clusterNum=5,d=data1,maxK=5,clusterAlg="hc",distance="pearson",title="GBM")
p_value0=survAnalysis(mainTitle="BRCA_CC",time=clinical_USE$time,status=clinical_USE$status,result0$group,
                      distanceMatrix=result0$distanceMatrix,similarity=TRUE)

2. use the mRNA and miRNA data for SNF

result1=ExecuteSNF(list(data1,data2), clusterNum=5, K=20, alpha=0.5, t=20)

p_value1=survAnalysis(mainTitle="BRCA_SNF",time=clinical_USE$time,status=clinical_USE$status,result1$group,
                      distanceMatrix=result1$distanceMatrix,similarity=TRUE)

3. use the mRNA, miRNA, LncRNA data for SNF

result2=ExecuteSNF(list(data1,data2,data3), clusterNum=5, K=20, alpha=0.5, t=20)
